{
  "texts": [
    "As both algorithms and cases become more complex, incorporating inputs of imaging, video, and genomics, it is essential that neurosurgeons consider the technical elements of the proposed methods.",
    "As large language models and ChatGPT begin to be translated to neurosurgery, the translation of these models should be clinician-led and necessitate clinical metrics to carefully validate these tools while developing them to improve the quality of care.",
    "Schonfeld et al.",
    "Cureus 16(1): e51963.",
    "DOI 10.7759/cureus.51963"
  ]
}